          {
            "title": "Intro",
            "id": 82602,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Sometimes we'll need to update data inside a string without creating a whole new string. Like updating a daily lunch special.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"special = \" /><text value=\"&quot;Today's special is pasta&quot;\" class=\"string\" /></content></code></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Replace",
            "id": 82603,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>We can replace a part of a string stored inside a variable by first coding the variable's name and the instruction <code>replace()</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"special = \" /><text value=\"&quot;Today's special is pasta&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"new_special = special.replace()\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"60\" endIndex=\"67\" /><option startIndex=\"67\" endIndex=\"68\" /><option startIndex=\"68\" endIndex=\"69\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>replace</code>, followed by <code>(</code>, and finally <code>)</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Values",
            "id": 82604,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Inside the parentheses, we add the part we want to replace, like <code>\"pasta\"</code>, a comma, and then the new value, <code>\"pizza\"</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"special = \" /><text value=\"&quot;Today's special is pasta&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"new_special = special.replace(\" /><text value=\"&quot;pasta&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\",\" /><text value=\"&quot;pizza&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"68\" endIndex=\"75\" /><option startIndex=\"75\" endIndex=\"76\" /><option startIndex=\"76\" endIndex=\"83\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>\"pasta\"</code>, followed by <code>,</code>, and finally <code>\"pizza\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Displaying",
            "id": 82628,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>By coding <code>print(new_special)</code>, we can see that the <code>new_special</code> variable contains the updated string.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"special = \" /><text value=\"&quot;Today's special is pasta&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"new_special = special.replace(\" /><text value=\"&quot;pasta&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\",\" /><text value=\"&quot;pizza&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(new_special)\" /><text type=\"break\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"86\" endIndex=\"91\" /><option startIndex=\"91\" endIndex=\"92\" /><option startIndex=\"92\" endIndex=\"103\" /><option startIndex=\"103\" endIndex=\"104\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Today's special is pizza\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>print</code> followed by <code>(</code> and then <code>new_special</code>, <code>)</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "No change",
            "id": 82630,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>By coding <code>print(special)</code>, we can see that the value of the original variable does not change.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"special = \" /><text value=\"&quot;Today's special is pasta&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"new_special = special.replace(\" /><text value=\"&quot;pasta&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\",\" /><text value=\"&quot;pizza&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(new_special)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(special)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"106\" endIndex=\"120\" /></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Today's special is pizza\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Today's special is pasta\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to type <code>print(special)</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Update",
            "id": 82629,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Instead of creating a new variable, we can reassign the original variable to the updated string by coding <code>special</code>. </p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"special = \" /><text value=\"&quot;Today's special is pasta&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"special = special.replace(\" /><text value=\"&quot;pasta&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\",\" /><text value=\"&quot;pizza&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(special)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"validatedInput\" isDefault=\"true\" startIndex=\"38\" endIndex=\"45\" /></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Today's special is pizza\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to type <code>special</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Occurrences ",
            "id": 82612,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>When we use <code>replace()</code> like this, we'll replace all occurrences of the value inside the string, we can see it here by coding <code>print(july)</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"june = \" /><text value=\"&quot;June sales target updated. Let's rock June!&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"july = june.replace(\" /><text value=\"&quot;June&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"&quot;July&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(july)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"91\" endIndex=\"96\" /><option startIndex=\"96\" endIndex=\"97\" /><option startIndex=\"97\" endIndex=\"101\" /><option startIndex=\"101\" endIndex=\"102\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"July sales target updated. Let's rock July!\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>print</code> followed by <code>(</code> and then <code>july</code>, <code>)</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
